'''Leverton Pierre''' (born 9 March 1998) is a Haitian professional [[association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[midfielder]] for [[Liga Portugal 2]] club [[F.C. Vizela|Vizela]] and the [[Haiti national football team|Haiti national team]].<ref>{{Soccerway|470890}}</ref>

==Club career==
Pierre signed his first professional contract with [[SC Bastia|Bastia]] on 29 July 2017, joining from the Haitian club CS Saint-Louis.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://haititempo.com/foot-france-transfert-leverton-pierre-18-ans-signe-un-contrat-stagiaire-pro-a-bastia/|title=Foot- France- Transfert : Leverton Pierre (18 ans) signe un contrat stagiaire-pro à Bastia - Haiti-Tempo|date=23 June 2016|publisher=}}</ref> He made his professional debut with [[AC Ajaccio|Ajaccio]] in a 2–0 loss to [[Valenciennes FC|Valenciennes]] on 16 February 2018.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.lfp.fr/ligue2/feuille_match/83456|title=LFP.fr - Ligue de Football Professionnel - Domino's Ligue 2 - Saison 2017/2018 - 26ème journée - Valenciennes FC / AC Ajaccio|website=www.lfp.fr}}</ref>

On 1 July 2025, Pierre signed for [[Liga Portugal 2]] club [[F.C. Vizela|Vizela]] for one season.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Chery |first=Manesson |date=1 July 2025 |title=Foot - Transfert : Leverton Pierre signe au Portugal |url=https://haititempo.com/foot-transfert-leverton-pierre-signe-au-portugal/ |access-date=11 July 2025 |website=Haiti-Tempo |language=en-US}}</ref>

==International career==
Pierre was part of the [[Haiti national under-20 football team]] that won the [[2017 CONCACAF U-20 Championship qualifying]] tournament, scoring one goal in the process.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://hpnhaiti.com/nouvelles/index.php/sport/23-football/1319-haiti-u20-coree-2017-haiti-a-etrille-anguilla-au-premier-match|title=Haiti Press Network - Haïti-U20-Corée 2017 : Haïti a étrillé Anguilla|first=Esther|last=Versiere|website=hpnhaiti.com}}{{Dead link|date=August 2025 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref> In May 2019, he was named to [[Haiti national football team|Haiti]]'s 40-man provisional squad for the [[2019 CONCACAF Gold Cup]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://gallery.mailchimp.com/78d3589fb61466b549ff752e5/files/041bd60a-92da-467b-b8d6-d6a51bae68bd/2019_Concacaf_Gold_Cup_Preliminary_Lists_May_20.pdf|date=20 May 2019|title=40-Player National Team Roster}}</ref> He debuted with the senior Haiti national team in a 1–0 [[2022 FIFA World Cup qualification]] loss to [[Canada men's national soccer team|Canada]] on 12 June 2021.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://int.soccerway.com/matches/2021/06/12/nc-america/wc-qualifying-concacaf/haiti/canada/3490513/|title=Haiti vs. Canada - 12 June 2021|website=Soccerway}}</ref>

